 offers a broad panorama of spiritual and devotional techniques of self-formation and subjectivation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aChristian life. 0aDevotional literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aSociety of Jesus. 4aSpiritual Exercises. 4aself-formation. 4asubjecthood. 4asubjectivization. 4atechniques. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226473048423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226473048.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles